About this hotel

Along a major thoroughfare, this relaxed hotel in a modern, Moorish-inspired building is 4 km from the ancient Saadian Tombs, 5 km from Jemaa el-Fnaa, an open-air marketplace, and 6 km from Marrakech Menara Airport.

Check-in time: 3:00 PM
Check-out time: 12:00 PM

    Mechouar-Kasbah

    Expansive Mechouar-Kasbah takes in part of the walled old town, plus the sprawling ruins of 16th-century El Badii Palace, and the Saadian Tombs mausoleum, with ornate pillars, tiles, and stucco. The Mellah, or Jewish quarter, is home to the restored Slat Al Azama Synagogue, said to date to 1492. Outside the walls, the extensive Agdal Gardens were laid out in the 12th century with citrus orchards and a vast pool.

    About this hotel

    Along a major thoroughfare, this relaxed hotel in a modern, Moorish-inspired building is 4 km from the ancient Saadian Tombs, 5 km from Jemaa el-Fnaa, an open-air marketplace, and 6 km from Marrakech Menara Airport. …

    Traditional rooms with Oriental carpets and tile floors offer free Wi-Fi and flat-screen TVs, as well as sitting areas, and balconies or terraces. The 1- and 2-bedroom suites add separate living rooms.

    Freebies include breakfast, parking and an airport shuttle. There’s an ornate Moroccan restaurant and a lounge, as well as an outdoor pool with a relaxed bar. A spa has a hammam and an indoor pool.
